<DOC><DOCNO> AP900608-0084 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-08-90 1106EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Obit-Isogai     06-08 0155</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Obit-Isogai,0161</SECOND><HEAD>Japanese Ambassador To Fiji Killed in Car Crash</HEAD><DATELINE>SUVA, Fiji (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Japanese Ambassador Toshio Isogai was killedwhen his car hit a utility pole while apparently trying to avoid acow that had strayed onto a road, embassy officials said today. Hewas 62.   The accident occurred late Thursday night near the town ofSigatoka, in the west of the main island, Viti Levu, the officialssaid.   The embassy said the ambassador's wife, Toshiko, was not injured.The couple's personal chef, Takashi Tabata, suffered a broken leg.   Isogai was born Aug. 24, 1927, in Okayama in western Japan. Hegraduated from the Agriculture-Fisheries College of Tokyo Universityin 1953 and entered the Foreign Ministry in 1956.   He served as consul general at the Japanese Consulate in Seattlefrom December 1982 to December 1986, when he was named ambassador toFiji.   In addition to his wife, Isogai is survived by a son.</TEXT></DOC>